IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: ALTERNATIVE GIFTS IS A NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATION WHICH INSPIRES SUPPORT FOR HUMANITARIAN AND ENVIRONMENTAL CAUSES.
IRS990.MissionDescription: ALTERNATIVE GIFTS IS A NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATION WHICH INSPIRES SUPPORT FOR HUMANITARIAN AND ENVIRONMENTAL CAUSES.
IRS990.Description: THE ORGANIZATION COLLECTS DONATIONS FROM THE GENERAL PUBLIC AND CONTRIBUTES TO OTHER CHARITABLE ORGANIZATIONS WHICH PROVIDE SPECIFIC SERVICES FOR WORLD RELIEF AND DEVELOPMENT. THE DONORS DESIGNATE THE RECIPIENT ORGANIZATIONS. THE ORGANIZATION RESEARCHES AND MONITORS THE RECEIVING ORGANIZATIONS. THE RECEIVING ORGANIZATIONS ARE REQUIRED TO PROVIDE SPECIFIC INFORMATION IN ORDER TO BE INCLUDED IN THE ORGANIZATIONS SUPPORT CATALOG. FOR THE YEAR ENDING JUNE 30, 2010, A TOTAL OF THIRTY-SEVEN OUTSIDE PROJECTS BENEFITTED FROM DONATIONS COLLECTED AND DISTRIBTUTED BY ALTERNATIVE GIFT MARKETS, INC. AND THREE INTERNAL PROJECTS WERE SUPPORTED.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE FORM 990 IS MADE AVAILABLE TO ALL BOARD MEMBERS. THE BOARD TREASURER REVIEWS AND HAS FINAL APPROVAL OF THE FORM 990 BEFORE FILING.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The board members are provided the conflict of interest statement at the annual board meeeting. All members are required to sign the document annually and return to the Organization.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15a
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The board reviews and approves the budget which includes officer compensation.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 18
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Organization's Form 990 is available upon request or on its website. The Organization's Form 1023 was lost during the Organization's move from California to Kansas. Attempts to obtain a copy of the form have been unsuccessful.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The organization makes its governing documents, conflict of interest policy and financial statements available to the public upon request at its administrative offices.

THE FINANCE COMMITTEE REVIEWS AND APPROVES THE AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AT A COMMITTEE MEETING. AT THIS MEETING, THE INDEPENDENT AUDITORS PRESENT THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS TO THE FINANCE COMMITTEE. AT THIS TIME COMMITTEE MEMBERS ASK QUESTIONS OR REQUEST FURTHER EXPLANATIONS. ONCE COMMITTEE MEMBERS ARE SATISFIED, THEY FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE APPROVED.
